reportilo: copyright and data rights
====================================

The reportilo source code (everything under R/, inst/shiny-apps/, tests/,
vignettes/ and the build scripts under data-raw/) is Copyright (c) 2026 Ahmad
Sofi-Mahmudi and is released under GPL-3 (see the LICENSE file).

reportilo also bundles data derived from third-party sources. The provenance and
the rights position for each bundled dataset are described below.


1. Guideline catalog metadata
------------------------------
Files: data/guidelines.rda, inst/extdata/guidelines.json
Source: the EQUATOR Network reporting guideline library
  (https://www.equator-network.org/).
Content: factual bibliographic metadata such as titles, acronyms, study designs,
  clinical areas, source URLs and identifiers (DOI, PubMed ID).
Rights: individual facts are not subject to copyright. reportilo's selection,
  normalization and arrangement of this metadata is released under GPL-3 with
  the rest of the package. Each entry links back to its EQUATOR source.


2. Reporting checklist item text
--------------------------------
Files: data/checklist_items.rda, inst/extdata/checklist_items.json
Source: the individual reporting guideline documents, each authored and
  copyrighted by its respective authors and publishers, and indexed by the
  EQUATOR Network. Every item records its source URL and parse provenance (see
  the parse_status dataset and reportilo_coverage()).
Rights: the wording of each reporting checklist remains the intellectual
  property of the respective guideline authors and publishers and is subject to
  their own terms. reportilo does not claim copyright over the underlying
  guideline text; it redistributes a normalized, machine-readable representation
  so researchers can fill the checklist in, and it links to each original
  source. Where a guideline's terms do not permit redistribution of its text,
  reportilo links to the source instead of bundling the item text.


3. Flow diagram and risk-of-bias templates
-------------------------------------------
Files: data/flowchart_*.rda, data/rob*.rda, inst/extdata/flowcharts.json,
  inst/extdata/rob.json
Content: structural templates (node and edge layouts, count fields, level
  definitions) for PRISMA 2020, CONSORT, STARD, common observational designs and
  common risk-of-bias tools. These templates were authored for reportilo and are
  released under GPL-3. They implement the structure described by the respective
  reporting guideline and risk-of-bias method authors, who retain rights to the
  underlying methods.


Removal requests
----------------
If you are a rightsholder and want bundled data changed or removed, contact
ahmad.pub@gmail.com and the affected data will be updated or removed.
